This paper presents a new question answering dataset covering 11 typologically diverse languages, which is relevant to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses data quality and linguistic analyses, which are relevant to AI (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the dataset is designed for information-seeking tasks. Finally, neural networks (cs.NE) may also be relevant as the paper mentions the use of models for multilingual modeling.
